      <p>(One of the answers)</p>
      <p>Well, assuming “everyday discussion” includes those of a
      political and/or religious nature, here are a few:</p>
      <ol>
        <li>Post hoc ergo propter hoc[1] fallacy. Literally, Latin
        for “after this, therefore because of this,” this fallacy
        occurs when people claim that just because two things
        happened in succession that ...</li>
      </ol>
